741876452.text: "Of interest, expression of FLAG-mTOR-T, but not GFP, rendered substantial resistance to rapamycin 's inhibitory effects on Cd induced demethylated-PP2Ac, phospho-PP2Ac, down-regulated PTEN, phospho-Akt, phospho-Erk1/2 and cleaved-caspase-3, leading to reduced apoptosis in Cd exposed PC12 cells, implying that rapamycin activates PP2A, upregulates PTEN and inactivates Akt, thereby inhibiting Cd induced activation of Erk1/2, as well as neuronal apoptosis, in an mTOR kinase activity dependent manner."
